doc_summary_long: The NHS has announced a ban on homeopathy and herbal medicine as they say it is 'misuse of scarce funds'. Officials today ruled that the treatments are among dozens of medicines which should not be funded by the health service. And NHS bodies will be told not to pay for a number of specific treatments, such as omega 3 supplements, lidocaine plasters and fentanyl painkillers.
doc_summary_short: The NHS has announced a ban on homeopathy and herbal medicine as they say it is 'misuse of scarce funds'.
doc_title: NHS to ban homeopathy and herbal medicine, as 'misuse of resources'
